	</td>
	<td class="alt1">
	
		
			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				<img class="inlineimg" src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/forums/images/icons/icon1.gif" alt="Post" border="0" />
				<strong>Loot & Greed.....Give me your thoughts</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>I wanted to get a general opinion from people about items that drop and how loot should be dealt.<br />
<br />
I'll give you what I believe but it would be good to hear what the general concencus is on this matter.<br />
<br />
Recently, on my server Fennin Ro, there was a group of people in Karnor(which I wasn't a part of, However a fellow priest who will remain nameless  was there.  This cleric was grouped with a friend of mine, a Ranger.  they were camping the tower for the Drolvarg captain spawn.  Loot was not specified beforehand.<br />
<br />
This group kills the Captain and he has the Rare drop, Lupine Dagger.  There is one ranger in the group.  For those of you ho are unaware, a Lupine dagger is pretty whoop ass 9/18 effect: Greater wolf form. it IS Ranger ONLY.<br />
<br />
THe item drops the group decides that it should go to the Ranger, seems logical enough.  However, the Cleric, begins to whine and forces a roll saying he could use that item  to trade for clerical things.   They all roll, a bard wins, the bard hands the dagger to the ranger.  CLeric bitches and moans, the whole friggin zone ends up getting involved, on the side of the ranger, until comes to a point the Ranger is fed up and gives the dagger to the whining cleric.<br />
--------------------------------------<br />
<br />
I have always been of the opinion that when I am grouped, even when loot is not specified beforehand, that anything that drops in which a specific class will use, it WILL always go to that person.  the only time I will roll on an item is when there is no one in the group that can use said item.  like a few days ago I won a soulbinder, which  is an SK only weapon.  there was no SK in group so the whole group rolled on it.<br />
<br />
Looking at that cleric makes me ashamed to be a member of the same class as him.  it made me ill to hear that these type of things are happening.  that a person would take away a piece of equipment that would better the class person you are grouped with.<br />
<br />
i know this type of bahavior goes on quite often but it truly makes me sad that people have become this greedy. No matter what group I am in I will always insist that loot first goes to those who would use it.<br />
<br />
BTW, this jacklip cleric ended up trading the dagger for an Iksar ceremonial chestplate. LMAO.  number 1 the dagger is far superior in trade value than that Chest piece.  Number 2 he stated he needed to dagger to trade for cleric equipment. I don't consider this BP cleric EQ, sure it would be nice to have afer all the tanks who can't heal get one first.  But it is a novelty item, not a necessary cleric piece.<br />
<br />
so, what say you clerics, how do you all feel on this subject?<br />
<br />
<br />
Bree Wyndsdale<br />
54th cleric of Fennin Ro</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
