		<div>Different strokes for different folks.<br />
In a pickup group we all roll on an item.<br />
For my regular group it goes to whoever can use it. Then we either sell it off and split the winnings or trade it for something we can use.<br />
<br />
However for this situation, once the bard won the lotto then the cleric had no say in the matter and I would have told him to shove it up his ???<br />
<br />
Once you win the lotto what you do with the item is your business NO ONE elses. If the bard wanted to give it to the ranger then so be it.<br />
<br />
Also always always state the looting options when we start the group or whenever someone new comes in. If they dont like the options then they can leave. If they agree to it then so be it.<br />
<br />
<br />
Terec Granitebeard<br />
32nd Dwarven Cleric of Underfoot<br />
Mith Marr</div>
