		<!-- message -->
		<div>  Heya Bree!  Nice to see a face I know on these boards   <img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" />  I do an awful lot more perusing then posting myself.<br />
  Anyways, I happened to be in zone when this particular incident occured, and I must say I was quite embarrassed of my class at that moment.  It seemed all the rangers in the zone were venting their frustration and complaining about "greedy clerics" after your friend let the zone know about what happened.  My beliefs are the same as yours, and in my experience with pick up groups it usually practiced that way as well.  All loot should go to those who need and will use.  If more than one person can use, then the item is rolled between them.  If no one can use, then everyone who hasn't gotten a uber item in that group yet rolls.  If something uber drops that can be used by a person who already has an uber item, then that person can't roll unless he puts his first item up for re-roll if he wins the current item.<br />
  Some might argue that everyone in a pick up group has an equal opportunity and equal deservedness on anything that drops, so everyone should roll on everything.  To these people I point to what Verant did in the planes.  Making all planar armor no drop, it made loot awarding in the planes much easier and PLooting less of a problem.  A planar item will always go to someone who can use.  Why should the Kunark loot be any different?  In a lot of cases this stuff is better than what we get in the planes.  Making the Kunark armor drops droppable, among the other uber loot, has been a debatable decision by Verant, but I think it was the right move.  Especially considering the faction issues with the VS dungeons, making it impossible for the evil races who wish to still visit Overthere get any loot from said dungeons except through gifts and trades.  And because getting this loot doesn't require the force of a large scale raid in most cases, there is more of a chance that something will drop that is unusable by the classes present.  Making it droppable, nothing is going to rot...<br />
  Okay, that's my 2 cp on the issue.  In my particular opinion, that cleric was very self-centered in his decision.  His name is pretty popular on Fennin for what he did, if he wasn't a cleric he'd probably have a lot of trouble finding groups anymore   <img src="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" /><br />
<br />
Naerik Sh'veran<br />
55 High Elf Templar of Tunare<br />
Fennin Ro server<br />
*Sacred Fyre*<br />
<br />
[This message has been edited by Naerik (edited 07-31-2000).]</div>
