A Warrior is in a AM group and the SMR drops. He wins it. Another player then procedes to whine about it etc etc. So the Warrior gives him the item. A couple of hours later they are both in the frenzy group, and the FBSS drops. This time the other player wins it. The tank asks the other guy if he can have it, as he gave the player a SMR. The player replies, better go practice your rolling.<br />
<br />
If people whine for no good reason, giving them an item will do nothing. I know this as I have done the same thing that Ranger did in the original post. They are just plain greedy, and will keep it up if all they have to do is whine to get an item at the end of the day. That Ranger got sucked in, next time he should just ignore the other player, or if not possible leave the group. And try and avoid grouping with that person again.<br />
<br />
Sometimes its better to just walk away from people like that and have an early night.<br />
