		<!-- message -->
		<div>Its so much easier grouping with ya guild - lewt rules just don't apply.<br />
<br />
In general in pickup groups the looting rules depends on the location and the group composition.  Certain dungeons are catered to drop certain classes armour and such.  Everyone rolling on an item is in general the safest method because it averages out the loot.  For example you might be in an area that is 60% tank (hybrids and such) loot, 40% pure caster lewt and 0% priest loot.  Now is it really fair to only have the classes who can use the item roll? if you are sharing everything fairly experience and loot then no because as we can see priest classes get jack diddly.  If it was a little more fair or the quality of said items in a low chance slot was high enough then it would be fair just to roll on what came up.<br />
<br />
The cleric had a right to roll on said item if there was also no understanding (or previous transaction) that all cleric loot would go to them.  His or other peoples motives might remain unclear, he might want to give it to a ranger guildmate (knowning that it would benifit someone he knew - something that most people would rather see i'm sure), he might want to swop it for an uber spell that would help everyone he groups with (mark of karn anyone?).<br />
<br />
That said if someone wins something its entirely upto them what they do with it.<br />
<br />
This is why grouping with ya guild/friends or making the loot rules aparant early on are of absolute importance<br />
</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
